Upstream attribution and license
================================

The Python files in this directory are byte-for-byte copies of the
`lib/` sources of SkyeShark's claudewave
(https://github.com/SkyeShark/claudewave), vendored at commit
6a40db17dc7a2bc36fce5695a8cd5ee0bb2b38be so that the cross-validation
harness (ports/claudewave/reference/run_upstream.py) is reproducible in
CI without a network fetch.

The upstream repository ships no standalone LICENSE file; its README.md
declares the license at the bottom:

    License: MIT.

and credits: "Created through iterative collaboration with Claude
(Opus 4.7) on a couple of songs."

